## `pub struct Watcher`
<!-- checksum: rust-watch-2 -->

### Postconditions
- Holds a `Receiver<Event>` and a slot id; when `Watcher` is dropped, the slot is removed from the registry.

### Public API

```rust
pub struct Watcher {
    rx: Receiver<Event>,
    slot_id: u64,
    registry: Arc<Mutex<WatchRegistry>>,
}

impl Watcher {
    pub fn try_recv(&self) -> Option<Event> {
        match self.rx.try_recv() {
            Ok(ev)                          => Some(ev),
            Err(TryRecvError::Empty)        => None,
            Err(TryRecvError::Disconnected) => None,
        }
    }

    pub fn recv(&self) -> Option<Event> {
        self.rx.recv().ok()
    }
}

impl Drop for Watcher {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        if let Ok(mut reg) = self.registry.lock() {
            reg.slots.retain(|s| s.id != self.slot_id);
        }
    }
}
```

### Failure Modes
None directly. `Filesystem::watch` surfaces `NotFound` / `NotADirectory` / `PermissionDenied` at construction time.

---

## `pub(crate) struct WatchRegistry` / `pub struct WatchMask`
<!-- checksum: rust-watch-3 -->

### Purpose
`WatchRegistry` is the internal store behind the `Filesystem`'s `Arc<Mutex<_>>`. `WatchMask` is a placeholder for future filtering (specific `EventKind`s); v2 watches every kind.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, Default)]
pub struct WatchMask;  // v2 placeholder — matches every EventKind

pub(crate) struct WatchSlot {
    pub id:         u64,
    pub path:       String,
    pub recursive:  bool,
    pub tx:         Sender<Event>,
}

pub(crate) struct WatchRegistry {
    next_id: u64,
    pub(crate) slots: Vec<WatchSlot>,
}

impl WatchRegistry {
    pub fn new() -> Self { Self { next_id: 1, slots: Vec::new() } }

    pub fn subscribe(
        registry: &Arc<Mutex<Self>>, path: String, recursive: bool,
    ) -> Watcher {
        let (tx, rx) = channel();
        let mut reg = registry.lock().expect("watch registry poisoned");
        let id = reg.next_id;
        reg.next_id += 1;
        reg.slots.push(WatchSlot { id, path, recursive, tx });
        Watcher { rx, slot_id: id, registry: Arc::clone(registry) }
    }

    pub fn emit(&self, ev: Event) {
        for slot in &self.slots {
            if !matches_slot(slot, &ev) { continue; }
            let _ = slot.tx.send(ev.clone());  // ignore disconnected
        }
    }
}

fn matches_slot(slot: &WatchSlot, ev: &Event) -> bool {
    // For "move" events, check both src and dst paths.
    let paths: Vec<&str> = match ev.kind {
        EventKind::Move => {
            let mut v = Vec::new();
            if let Some(s) = ev.src_path.as_deref() { v.push(s); }
            if let Some(s) = ev.dst_path.as_deref() { v.push(s); }
            if v.is_empty() { v.push(&ev.path); }
            v
        }
        _ => vec![ev.path.as_str()],
    };
    paths.iter().any(|p| path_matches(p, &slot.path, slot.recursive))
}

fn path_matches(event_path: &str, watched: &str, recursive: bool) -> bool {
    let parent = parent_of_path(event_path);
    if recursive {
        // Event path (or any ancestor) equals or descends into the watched dir.
        event_path.starts_with(watched)
            && (event_path.len() == watched.len()
                || event_path.as_bytes().get(watched.len()) == Some(&b'/')
                || watched == "/")
            && event_path != watched
    } else {
        parent == watched
    }
}

fn parent_of_path(p: &str) -> &str {
    match p.rfind('/') {
        Some(0)   => "/",
        Some(idx) => &p[..idx],
        None      => "/",
    }
}
```

### Invariants
- Event timestamps are non-decreasing within a single `Watcher` (the registry emits in mutation order; each channel preserves send order).
- Events are not dropped as long as the consumer keeps pace (channels are unbounded).

